these past couple of days...

305
00:15:13,481 --> 00:15:16,785
I'm starting to get the idea you mess
around with girls' hearts all the time.

306
00:15:16,810 --> 00:15:18,945
And I just thought you were more trustworthy than that.

307
00:15:18,970 --> 00:15:22,289
I am trustworthy! I promise I can be faithful-mii!

308
00:15:22,804 --> 00:15:25,073
Okay... Then what's my name?

309
00:15:25,098 --> 00:15:26,203
Ah...

310
00:15:26,287 --> 00:15:27,258
Uh...

311
00:15:27,953 --> 00:15:29,815
It's uh... Sanae!

312
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:30,885
I'm going home.

313
00:15:32,698 --> 00:15:34,467
But I was so close...

314
00:15:34,932 --> 00:15:35,446
Mii...

315
00:15:35,816 --> 00:15:37,239
Nothing happened at all?

316
00:15:37,657 --> 00:15:38,471
You're sure?

317
00:15:38,496 --> 00:15:42,496
Something almost happened, but rest
assured, absolutely nothing happened.

318
00:15:42,521 --> 00:15:43,326
Well that's good.

319
00:15:43,351 --> 00:15:44,715
You're next, Lord Moffle.

320
00:15:44,740 --> 00:15:45,913
High school...

321
00:15:45,938 --> 00:15:47,840
That sure brings back memories.

322
00:15:47,993 --> 00:15:52,315
I went to a strict boarding school
called Fuwafuwa Military Academy.

323
00:15:52,340 --> 00:15:54,269
The upperclassmen were all so...

324
00:15:54,294 --> 00:15:55,037
I've heard enough.

325
00:15:55,062 --> 00:15:55,655
Moff?

326
00:15:55,780 --> 00:15:57,488
Just get through it with no trouble.

327
00:16:02,448 --> 00:16:04,130
What the moff is going on?

328
00:16:04,155 --> 00:16:07,071
I don't know. They just asked us to meet them here.

329
00:16:07,096 --> 00:16:08,426
Kanie and Sento...

330
00:16:08,451 --> 00:16:12,173
I heard one of my classmates got
her feelings hurt by you two jerks.

331
00:16:12,261 --> 00:16:13,870
And what's that weird thing on your head?

332
00:16:14,303 --> 00:16:15,730
Moff-just ignore it...

333
00:16:15,755 --> 00:16:17,879
Anyway, I don't understand what you're mad about...

334
00:16:17,925 --> 00:16:18,688
Don't play dumb!

335
00:16:19,002 --> 00:16:21,810
It's okay Terano, it really doesn't bother me that much.

336
00:16:21,835 --> 00:16:22,971
Doesn't bother you?

337
00:16:22,996 --> 00:16:26,300
I thought you said this guy tried to put
the moves on you in the stairwell yesterday!

338
00:16:26,390 --> 00:16:31,228
That Sento girl and some first-year
named Chujo are both Kanie's girlfriends.

339
00:16:31,253 --> 00:16:33,329
They worked together to break your heart!

340
00:16:33,431 --> 00:16:35,899
But I... but I never said that!

341
00:16:36,007 --> 00:16:37,686
But that's pretty much what happened.

342
00:16:37,821 --> 00:16:43,585
That's ridiculous! I swear upon the Goddess Libra
that Kanie and I have done no such thing to this girl!

343
00:16:43,687 --> 00:16:47,315
And you expect me to believe that? Besides, who's Libra?

344
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:50,880
If you wish to behold the wrath
of Libra, then I'll show it to you.

345
00:16:51,204 --> 00:16:52,213
What are you doing?

346
00:16:52,238 --> 00:16:53,222
Hold it... moff.

347
00:16:53,427 --> 00:16:54,424
Are you sure?

348
00:16:54,725 --> 00:16:55,740
What's with the "moff" thing?

349
00:16:55,765 --> 00:16:56,383
Let me handle this.

350
00:16:56,407 --> 00:16:57,615
Whatever, I don't care.

351
00:16:57,640 --> 00:16:59,724
Just hurry up and apologize to Kanae. Right now!

352
00:16:59,781 --> 00:17:00,602
I'm sorry.

353
00:17:00,638 --> 00:17:03,888
Eh, moff, who cares about the kid's pride, anyway?

354
00:17:04,510 --> 00:17:06,215
No way. I want you to grovel!

355
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:07,687
Okay... how's this?

356
00:17:07,712 --> 00:17:08,676
Too easy!

357
00:17:08,821 --> 00:17:09,861
Where's your pride?

358
00:17:09,893 --> 00:17:12,032
Don't you dare talk to her ever again!

359
00:17:12,161 --> 00:17:16,377
As moff as my witness, from the bottom
of my heart, I really do apologize.

360
00:17:16,564 --> 00:17:17,646
No... wait...

361
00:17:17,734 --> 00:17:20,028
I'm starting to think he's making fun of us.

362
00:17:20,124 --> 00:17:21,965
No, I honestly feel bad about it.

363
00:17:22,070 --> 00:17:24,617
Yeah right. You're just saying whatever you have to say!

364
00:17:24,642 --> 00:17:27,471
You obviously don't care about
this poor girl's feelings for you!

365
00:17:27,496 --> 00:17:30,837
I mean nothing you've said or done
has had a shred of sincerity to it!

366
00:17:30,893 --> 00:17:33,237
It's like you knocked it off from a TV show!

367
00:17:35,211 --> 00:17:36,086
You...

368
00:17:37,251 --> 00:17:39,027
You just said the worst thing possible.

369
00:17:39,052 --> 00:17:39,595
Huh?

370
00:17:40,146 --> 00:17:43,087
Hearing the word "knock-off"
is extremely problematic for him.

371
00:17:43,112 --> 00:17:46,074
I have had enough of you
arrogant bitches and your bullshit!

372
00:17:46,718 --> 00:17:49,049
Running your mouths about love and sincerity...

373
00:17:49,113 --> 00:17:51,678
You can't just throw those
words around like they're nothing!

374
00:17:52,041 --> 00:17:53,461
You're a bunch of kids!

375
00:17:53,535 --> 00:17:54,604
Don't make me laugh.

376
00:17:54,629 --> 00:17:57,157
You three don't know the first moffin' thing about love!

377
00:17:57,182 --> 00:17:58,957
Please don't get upset, Lord Moffle.

378
00:17:58,982 --> 00:18:03,796
You date some boy you barely know, you think you're
in love, then you complain about heartbreak afterwards?!

379
00:18:04,174 --> 00:18:05,746
You think life's that easy?!

380
00:18:06,306 --> 00:18:10,283
What, does it make you feel cool to pretend
to be angry for your friend's sake, is that it?

381
00:18:10,313 --> 00:18:11,779
You're full of it!

382
00:18:16,249 --> 00:18:17,077
Whoa!

383
00:18:17,537 --> 00:18:19,978
When the pain is bad enough to
make you wish you were dead...

384
00:18:20,239 --> 00:18:23,050
THAT... THAT'S what love is!

385
00:18:23,214 --> 00:18:26,815
Wait 'til the woman you've loved for over
ten years gets married to some bastard you hate!

386
00:18:26,844 --> 00:18:29,463
You can't even imagine the agony I felt that day!

387
00:18:29,531 --> 00:18:33,327
And then ten years later, she comes
and asks me to take care of her daughter?

388
00:18:33,553 --> 00:18:35,149
Do you know how that feels?!

389
00:18:35,274 --> 00:18:36,952
No! Because you're children!

390
00:18:36,979 --> 00:18:37,886
Wait a minute sir.

391
00:18:37,911 --> 00:18:40,116
Is this in reference to Princess Latifah's mother?

392
00:18:40,439 --> 00:18:42,830
Shut the moff up, it's hypothetical!

393
00:18:42,855 --> 00:18:44,004
What's his problem?!

394
00:18:44,157 --> 00:18:46,015
Yeah. He's really creeping me out.

395
00:18:46,045 --> 00:18:47,455
And what does "moff" mean?

396
00:18:47,504 --> 00:18:48,696
Stop it, guys!

397
00:18:50,764 --> 00:18:51,597
Kimura!

398
00:18:52,071 --> 00:18:52,981
I'm sorry...

399
00:18:53,139 --> 00:18:55,783
The only reason Kanie acted like that was for my sake!

400
00:18:55,808 --> 00:18:56,591
Huh?!

401
00:18:57,162 --> 00:19:01,527
He said all those crazy things and acted like a
scumbag on purpose to make Tsuchida hate his guts!

402
00:19:01,862 --> 00:19:04,257
That way maybe she'd want to be with me instead!

403
00:19:05,128 --> 00:19:06,254
Right, Kanie?

404
00:19:06,335 --> 00:19:08,558
I what...? Uhhh, yeah...

405
00:19:08,637 --> 00:19:12,142
When I asked Kanie for advice about how
to patch everything up with Tsuchida...

406
00:19:12,375 --> 00:19:17,202
he had a plan... He said the only way to get things
back to normal was to make her not like him anymore.

407
00:19:17,423 --> 00:19:20,192
I know this mess ended up making me look bad too...

408
00:19:20,217 --> 00:19:23,201
But I swear I'll try really
hard to be the best guy for you.

409
00:19:23,226 --> 00:19:25,473
So do you think maybe you could give me a chance?

410
00:19:25,569 --> 00:19:28,495
O-okay... If you're sure that's what you want too.

411
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:31,408
Well then if the two of you don't
have anything left to be upset over...

412
00:19:31,433 --> 00:19:33,383
I guess I have nothing to say.

413
00:19:33,474 --> 00:19:34,215
Awesome!

414
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:36,267
Thank you for understanding!

415
00:19:36,307 --> 00:19:37,943
It's nice to have friends, huh?

416
00:19:44,428 --> 00:19:45,924
Thanks for the heads-up, Chujo...

417
00:19:46,554 --> 00:19:48,038
It all worked out, thanks to you.

418
00:19:48,332 --> 00:19:51,512
Sure... I knew something weird must be going on...

419
00:19:51,647 --> 00:19:54,452
It's a good thing I was able to get in contact with you.

420
00:19:54,931 --> 00:19:56,165
I appreciate it.

421
00:19:56,497 --> 00:19:59,920
Hopefully I can figure out a way
to explain all this to Kimura later.

422
00:19:59,992 --> 00:20:03,096
I'm surprised you didn't get mad
at Mr. Moffle and the other two.

423
00:20:03,468 --> 00:20:06,145
You almost made a lot of enemies because of this mess.

424
00:20:06,196 --> 00:20:07,776
Nah... I'm not mad...

425
00:20:08,025 --> 00:20:10,996
Either way, those idiots only did
it because they wanted to help me out.

426
00:20:11,269 --> 00:20:12,539
How could I be mad at that?

427
00:20:14,655 --> 00:20:15,021
What?

428
00:20:15,329 --> 00:20:16,053
Oh it's nothing.

429
00:20:16,078 --> 00:20:19,880
I was just thinking how you
reacted the way I expected you would.

430
00:20:19,905 --> 00:20:20,379
Huh?

431
00:20:20,606 --> 00:20:21,780
It's no big deal...

432
00:20:21,844 --> 00:20:22,992
I gotta go!

433
00:20:30,397 --> 00:20:31,887
Sento. You made it.

434
00:20:32,681 --> 00:20:34,659
It's good to see that you're back on the job...

435
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:36,625
I take it you've fully recovered then.

436
00:20:36,942 --> 00:20:40,764
Look at this, Lady Isuzu... Sir Kanie is very peculiar!

437
00:20:41,331 --> 00:20:42,388
Did something happen?

438
00:20:42,649 --> 00:20:47,877
Just look at the way he tries his best to preserve
the strawberry on top until the last possible moment!

439
00:20:48,427 --> 00:20:49,589
What? Is that weird?

440
00:20:50,009 --> 00:20:52,923
You appear to be healthy enough
to return to school tomorrow.

441
00:20:53,394 --> 00:20:55,333
Oh yeah. I'm perfectly fine now...

442
00:20:55,413 --> 00:20:56,668
Sorry for the trouble. Sento.

443
00:20:57,252 --> 00:21:00,622
No... I probably wasn't of
very much help to you in the end.

444
00:21:00,747 --> 00:21:02,898
In fact, I may have caused YOU trouble.

445
00:21:04,133 --> 00:21:07,006
Well, you can fill me in later... Are you hungry?

446
00:21:07,545 --> 00:21:09,241
Yes, we have croquettes!

447
00:21:09,388 --> 00:21:10,313
Thank you.

448
00:21:10,601 --> 00:21:13,750
Speaking of which, I've thought of a new croquette recipe!

449
00:21:14,152 --> 00:21:19,561
If I add sugar to the batter... they'll be even more
appealing to visitors with a sweet tooth won't they?

450
00:21:19,764 --> 00:21:23,365
Sounds good... I think the Maple
Kitchen could benefit from a new menu item.

451
00:21:23,530 --> 00:21:28,677
Then would it be alright if you sampled the new recipe to
make sure it's perfect before we serve it to the guests?

452
00:21:28,789 --> 00:21:30,952
Oh I get it. So I'm a guinea pig now.

453
00:21:30,977 --> 00:21:33,184
Oh no...! I didn't mean it that way!

454
00:21:34,091 --> 00:21:34,939
It's fine.

455
00:21:34,964 --> 00:21:37,535
Then I'll go ahead and make a
few first thing in the morning.

456
00:21:37,835 --> 00:21:38,978
Can't wait to try 'em.

457
00:21:39,003 --> 00:21:39,802
Perfect!

458
00:21:39,850 --> 00:21:41,403
I'm sure you'll like them.

459
00:22:08,575 --> 00:22:10,629
It's not good enough!

460
00:23:43,123 --> 00:23:45,145
Time for the attractions spotlight.

461
00:23:46,098 --> 00:23:48,328
Today's feature is Save the Earth.

462
00:23:48,414 --> 00:23:51,198
It's a fun-filled presentation about Earth science.

463
00:23:51,476 --> 00:23:53,967
Oh okay, so it's like a documentary type thing?

464
00:23:54,113 --> 00:23:59,462
Sort of. The audience experiences a lengthy
lecture from Future the globe about the many ways...

465
00:23:59,487 --> 00:24:01,885
in which humanity destroys our precious planet.

466
00:24:01,918 --> 00:24:03,878
That doesn't sound fun at all.

467
00:24:03,916 --> 00:24:07,635
And then after the show, he demands a
2,000 yen donation from each visitor.

468
00:24:07,701 --> 00:24:09,365
We should shut that down!

